HEADWORD: Lighterage
<hw>Light"er*age</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧t"⟦etil⟧r*⟦asl⟧j; 48)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The price paid for conveyance of goods on
a lighter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of unloading into a lighter, or of conveying
by a lighter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lighterman</ent>⟦br⟧
